 Permalink Reply by Billy Park Whyde on May 6, 2012 at 12:09pm 

I'd hold out  on retiring  or least think very very hard about it! I know of individuals that couldn't wait to retire and found out being with the wife 24/7 isn't as easy as the work was. Ya normally see these guys at Walmart saying Welcome to Walmart! Selling mineral rights is a one time deal with no turning back. With a lease you might if worded right get a decent bonus and possibly renewal payment or another lease plus royalty
 You might consider selling the property outright with mineral rights included which opens the door to speculators also.




 
▶ Reply

 



 Permalink Reply by Kathleen on May 6, 2012 at 2:20pm 

I personally would wait at least a year and see what shell does. 156,000.00 is good money but you could do better. If I was to sell them I would contact an auction house and see if they are interested. I really think 156 thousand for 52 acres of minerals seems low.
Recently someone sold theirs already leased for more at auction. The link was on this site but I don't remember where right now. If I remember right it was 100 acres and they got 3800.00 per acre. That would be 41,600 more minus the auction fee. If the drilling picks up and the numbers are good in your area these numbers could even go higher and you wouldn't have the tax burden of the royalties.
Everyone has their own personal thought on this topic with some people saying never sell. I think if someone really thinks about it, looks at it in all directions and still wants to sell than they should sell.



 
